      "content": "Your sense of being trapped and unseen by people you trust is incredibly painful, and it makes no sense why adults who aren't seeing your eyes in real-time can seem like the only people you can go to. Please understand that the overwhelming noise you hear right now doesn't predict your future; trauma and bullying can make you feel stuck in a loop, but that isn't how your brain actually works. Reaching out to a crisis line text a professional who is trained to hold space for exactly this kind of specific pain, and clarify to them that you need an answer to these immediate feelings rather than someone offering solutions.",
